  "prompt": "Do snakes really take revenge?",
  "response": "Snakes do not take revenge. Revenge is a complex behavior that requires a level of cognitive processing and emotional complexity not found in snakes. These reptiles are generally driven by basic survival instincts, such as finding food, reproducing, and avoiding predators. If a snake bites, it is typically because it feels threatened, is provoked, or is trying to capture prey. Any notion of a snake seeking revenge is more likely a projection of human emotions onto animal behavior rather than an action based on the snake\u2019s motivation.",
